#%Module1.0

module-whatis           "PRRTE is the PMIx Reference RunTime Environment"
module-url              "https://docs.prrte.org/en/latest/"
module-license          "$PREFIX/share/doc/prrte/LICENSE"
module-maintainer       "Marc Caubet Serrabou <marc.caubet@psi.ch>"

module-help             "
PRRTE is the process runtime and launcher infrastructure used by Open MPI and PMIx-based applications.

It provides commands such as 'prterun' to start parallel jobs, handles process placement and environment
setup across nodes, and integrates with resource managers such as Slurm. In a scheduled environment,
PRRTE can obtain the allocated hosts and process counts directly from the scheduler, so users can often
launch with a simple 'prterun ./application'.
"
